 IAM policies structure 

  are made in json
  
  -consist of:
      . Version: policy lenguage version, alwas include "2012-10-17"
      . Id: "s3-Account-Permissiones"
      . Statement: oner or more individual statements (required)

   -Statements consist of:
      . Sid: and indentifier for the Statement(optional)
      .Effect: wheter the statement allosws or denies acces (Allow, Deny)
      .Principal: accouent/user/ role to which this policy applied optional
      .Action: List of actiones this polici allows or denies
      .Condition: conditions for when this policy is in efect (optional)


example:

 {
    "Version": "2012-10-17",
    "Id": "s3-Account-Permissions",
    "Statement": [
        {
            "Sid": "1",
            "Effect": "Allow",
            "Principal": {
                "AWS": ["arn:aws:iam::12345156135:root"]
            },
            "Action": [
                "s3:GetObject",
                :s3:PutObject
            ],
            "Resource": ["arn:aws:s3:::mybucket/*"]
          }
    ]
  }
